Apple, Microsoft, Palantir Lead Wedbush Top Tech Picks Amid Iran Tensions
Nauman Khan
Thu, March 5, 2026 at 9:59 AM MST
This article first appeared on
.
Amid ongoing geopolitical friction with Iran, Wedbush Securities highlighted Apple (
), Microsoft (
), ServiceNow (NOW), and seven other tech firms as top picks to navigate market uncertainty.
The analysts
these companies as defensive names with resilient business models, pointing to exposure in cybersecurity and government contracts. Palantir (
) is singled out for its AI-powered platform, which is increasingly used in U.S. federal defense projects.
Cybersecurity leaders also featured heavily. CrowdStrike (
) is recognized for its Falcon platform, which leverages AI to counter modern cyber threats, while Palo Alto Networks (
) benefits from rising demand for AI-driven enterprise security. Check Point Software (
) is positioned to expand its AI-enhanced security offerings across SASE, ERM, and email protection.
Microsoft is actually in the lead because it has a cloud and AI war chest of $ 625 billion, whereas Apple has a strong selection of devices in its stable and a healthy cash flow, making it an easy target for low-risk investments.
